  "prompt": "Is there such a thing as an agnostic theist?",
  "response": "Yes, the term \"agnostic theist\" refers to someone who believes in the existence of a god or gods but also considers the nature or existence of this divinity as ultimately unknowable or uncertain. This position combines elements of theism with agnosticism. An agnostic theist might have faith in a higher power while admitting the limitations of human understanding or the lack of empirical evidence to definitively know the nature of such a power.",
